        back in the year 2000 here in the u.s., we had a plethora of fantastic talent that were pumping out memorable hits and unforgettable sales and chart stats. but looking back on that year today i have to say, in my honest opinion, no act could top nsync! their 'no strings attached' album turns 23 next month *i can't believe it!* during this time that year their first single 'bye bye bye' was staying put in the hot 100's top 10 and nsync gave a fantastic performance in jan at the ama's. and their fans couldn't wait to buy their upcoming album ;).

        i still remember that album locking the #1 spot on the billboard 200 albums chart for a solid 8 straight wks and selling like crazy! it went 10x pla. in something like 3 months! it still holds the guinness record as the fastest selling pop album in u.s. history *basically it reached diamond status faster than any other album in u.s. history, 3 months!...and given all the big selling albums we've had over the years, that's a HUGE compliment!*

        i can't say i was a big nsync fan back then, but i can't lie, justin timberlake has a been a fun ride on the charts, esp. the hot 100, for me all these years. here's the big hit singles off the 'no strings attached' album:

        1. 'bye bye bye-#4 hot 100' *jan.* : nsync opened the 2000 ama's *check it out on youtube* with their new single and i recall it going in the top 10 very fast. their vid would be #1 on trl just about every day...already building their much anticipated comeback *their fans @ the time were mad nysnc hadn't made any new music since their xmas & debut albums both in 1998*. so on the first day the album was officially in stores, it sold 1.1. mill. copies in 1 day! unheard of back then! nsync was the very first & still the only act to sell 1mill+ albums in 1 day over here. and they sold something like 2.3 mill. in the first wk...believe me, that was an amazing achievement. https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=C27NShgTQE4

        2. 'it's gonna be me-#1 hot 100' *may, literally LOL!*: first time i ever saw justin timberlake @ #1 LOL! so when this is #1 over here, nsync is literally the HOTTEST act in the u.s.! can't say it any other way! their album is pumping around 1-2mill. copies every wk! i still remember their shelves being empty very fast @ the music stores. i mean, i recall that other artists who had albums coming out that year would have those albums wait while nsync's momentum cooled down. in may of 2000 their album is already closing in on 10x plat. *diamond*! great memories! https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=uWuNCQRcy7M

        3. 'this i promise you-#5 hot 100' *sept.*: so during this time, not only was their album selling like hotcakes nsync even had the 'no strings attached tour' *if memory serves me right* that sold out in 1 day! and these venues were all football stadiums! i remember it being called a 'stadium only' tour back then. the momentum nsync had that year was just crazy! so it's no surprise they would get billboard's coveted #1 album of the year, as well as numerous other music awards. enjoy everyone! https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=eqC4xFqjalM
